# .makeignore.example - Example patterns for excluding Makefile directories
# ==========================================================================
# Copy this file to .make/.makeignore and uncomment the patterns you need
#
# PURPOSE:
# This file controls which directories containing Makefiles should be excluded
# from the main Makefile's auto-discovery and inclusion system.
#
# IMPORTANT: Only include directories that might actually contain Makefiles.
# Directories like .git, node_modules, __pycache__, etc. will never contain
# Makefiles, so there's no need to list them here.
#
# FORMAT RULES:
# - One pattern per line
# - Lines starting with # are comments
# - Empty lines are ignored
# - Patterns match directory names relative to project root
# - Use * for wildcards (shell glob patterns)
# - Patterns are case-sensitive
# ==========================================================================

