# ==========================================================================
# USAGE TIPS:
# ==========================================================================
#
# 1. Only uncomment patterns for directories that:
#    - Actually exist in your project
#    - Contain or might contain Makefiles
#    - Should not be included in the main build
#
# 2. Test your configuration:
#    make list-subdirs   # Shows included directories
#    make list-ignored   # Shows what's being ignored
#
# 3. Common use cases:
#    - Exclude test directories with separate test runners
#    - Exclude experimental code not ready for production
#    - Exclude examples that shouldn't run with main build
#    - Exclude vendor code with its own build system
#    - Exclude deployment configs managed separately
#
# 4. Remember: .makeignore only affects auto-discovery.
#    You can still run make directly in ignored directories.
#
# 5. For monorepos: Use patterns like 'packages/*/test' to exclude
#    test directories within all packages
#
# 6. Version control: Consider tracking .makeignore.example but
#    not .makeignore if team members need different configs
#
# ==========================================================================